The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Birla Corp claws back into the black

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Jan. 31: Birla Corporation has posted a net profit of Rs 5.95 crore in the third quarter ended December 31 compared with a loss of Rs 2.92 crore during the corresponding period last fiscal.

 The cash profit increased by 163 per cent to Rs 14.5 crore from Rs 5.51 crore in the year-ago period. The turnover of the company registered a growth of 16 per cent at Rs 326.78 crore against Rs 281.63 crore.

 The company is setting up a unit ? Durga Hitech Cement ? near its existing plant at Durgapur to manufacture 1 million tonnes of Portland Pozzolona cement. It is also setting up two captive power plants of 27 MW each at Satna in Madhya Pradesh and Chanderia in Rajasthan.

 For the nine-month period ended December 31, the turnover of the company grew by 17 per cent at Rs 1,013.72 crore against Rs 863.43 crore during the same period last year. The net profit increased five times to Rs 48.73 crore, while there was an increase of 6.49 per cent in the volumes of the cement division.

 Srei net leaps

 Srei Infrastructure Finance Limited has registered a 115 per cent jump in its profit after tax at Rs 8.78 crore for the third quarter ended December 31 compared with Rs 4.09 crore in the corresponding period last financial year.

 Profit before tax grew by 114 per cent at Rs 13.64 crore for the third quarter against Rs 6.38 crore in the year-ago period.

 Total income of the company increased by 20 per cent to Rs 35.66 crore from Rs 29.77 crore in the same period last fiscal.

 For the nine-month period ended December 31, the company?s net profit after tax grew 56 per cent at Rs 18.10 crore against Rs 11.58 crore in the previous fiscal. 




